
@startuml

' Classes
class Doctor {
  -practitionerNumber: String
  -fullName: String
  -address: String
  -phoneNumber: String
  -signature: Image
}

class Patient {
  -healthNumber: String
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -address: String
  -phoneNumber: String
}

class Test {
  -testId: String
  -name: String
  -duration: Integer
  -isAppointmentRequired: Boolean
  -isSampleDropoff: Boolean
  -testGroup: String
}

class Requisition {
  -requisitionId: String
  -validFrom: Date
  -repeatCount: Integer
  -repeatInterval: String (weekly, monthly, etc.)
  -doctor: Doctor
  -patient: Patient
  -tests: List<Test>
}

class Appointment {
  -appointmentId: String
  -confirmationNumber: String
  -startDate: Date
  -startTime: Time
  -endTime: Time
  -labName: String
  -labRegistrationNumber: String
  -requisition: Requisition
  -lab: Lab
}

class Lab {
  -labId: String
  -name: String
  -registrationNumber: String
  -address: String
  -businessHoursStart: Time
  -businessHoursEnd: Time
  -cancellationFee: Double
}

class TestResult {
  -resultId: String
  -test: Test
  -requisition: Requisition
  -result: String (positive/negative)
  -report: String
}

' Relationships
Doctor "1" --> "0..*" Requisition : creates
Patient "1" --> "0..*" Requisition : submits
Requisition "1" --> "1" Doctor : prescribedBy
Requisition "1" --> "1" Patient : belongsTo
Requisition "1" --> "1..*" Test : includes
Test "1" --> "0..*" Requisition : includedIn
Test "1" --> "0..*" Appointment : scheduledFor
Appointment "1" --> "1" Lab : at
Appointment "1" --> "1" Requisition : for
Lab "1" --> "0..*" Appointment : provides
TestResult "1" --> "1" Test : relatesTo
TestResult "1" --> "1" Requisition : relatesTo
Doctor "1" --> "0..*" TestResult : views
Patient "1" --> "0..*" TestResult : views

@enduml

---

### ✅ Summary of Key Elements:
- **Doctor**: Manages requisitions and must provide personal info and digital signature.
- **Patient**: Submits requisitions and can make appointments or drop off samples.
- **Test**: Has a group, duration, and whether it needs an appointment or sample drop-off.
- **Requisition**: Contains tests from the same group, may be repeated, and links doctor and patient.
- **Appointment**: Made by patients for tests requiring one; has confirmation details and lab info.
- **Lab**: Provides all tests, defines hours and fees.
- **TestResult**: Stores test outcome and report, accessible to both doctor and patient.

